  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assembly Operator (Night Shift)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Ensure the safe operation of equipment used in product manufacturing. </li><li>Conduct regular checks to verify that all safety features are in place and functional.</li><li>Maintain a clean, organized, and safe work area in accordance with 6S standards.</li><li>Immediately report to the direct supervisor if any safety feature is not working or has been altered in any way.</li><li>Adhere to company and departmental regulations and follow all assigned job responsibilities.</li><li>Perform all operations strictly in accordance with Work Instructions.</li><li>Complete any additional tasks or assignments as directed by the supervisor.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Nitec in any discipline or equivalent.</li><li>Process 1 years of relevant work experience in assembly line is preferred.</li><li>Those without experience are welcome to apply as training will be provided.</li><li>Able to perform night shift.</li></ul><p>Interested applicants are welcome to send your resume to career@oneconsulting-global.com</p><p><br /></p><p>EA Personnel: R1107675</p><p>Agency no. 07C3676</p>",
